<br>
I am not leaving.<br>
<br>
I am an American citizen, born and bred.  I respect the ideals this country was founded on, but has never truly achieved - freedom, equality, and individual rights.  I will continue to criticize the policies of our government that run counter to those ideals.  I will continue to vote with my conscience, and vocally criticize our foreign policy, protest discrimination in any form, and stand my ground when I am told by everyone from my next door neighbor to the President that my religion is invalid, evil, and should be made illegal to practice.<br>
<br>
I am not leaving.<br>
<br>
I respect my country, even though I rarely agree with our government.  I have no problem with Christianity in the slightest.<br>
<br>
But this is my country too, and just as you are entitled you your opinion, I'm bloody well entitled to mine.<br>
<br>
I'm not leaving.  Deal.<br>
<br>
