I recently finished my active duty in the Marines.  Let me tell you, it sucks.  No, I enjoyed my time in the military (for the most part), so this isn't from some whiner.  This is from someone who got screwed over continuously by something he felt the deepest love for and greatest pride in.<br>
<br>
I'll badmouth the government's decisions all I want.  I'll also hold the opinion that all the little angsty teenagers who pretend to know what anarchy is can STFU or leave.  I'll dance both sides of this argument because I have seen both sides, and both have viable points.<br>
<br>
You tell me to respect the President because of his station and I will laugh.  He is a man, just like any other, and he earns his respect.<br>
<br>
You tell me to respect the Flag and I will stand at attention with a tear in my eye, because that flag was bought in blood and it will die in blood.<br>
<br>
Telling someone to leave the country if they don't like it is a little harsh, but so is turning a blind eye on your country's failings.  Especially with outside observation, we can learn who we are and strive to improve those areas in which we're lacking. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mistressoftherose>Mistress of the Rose</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Black Rose</span><br>  Posts: 785<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/19/03 4:08:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm62.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://noirdaila.homestead.com/files/ZDoll.JPG width=83 height=154></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: God and America</span><hr size=1> Robin I dare say you insult America by saying our abilities to argue are akin to Crossfire.  I know high schoolers who debate better than that!<br>
